          <title>Florida seeks easier voting access for hurricane-displaced citizens</title>
          <description><![CDATA[Last year's hurricanes displaced thousands of Floridians, turning their lives upside down and making it even harder for some to vote during a crucial election year. Now, a Pinellas County state lawmaker wants to make it easier for people to cast their ballots after a storm.]]></description>
